      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant paired with a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle. This 996.2 generation benefits from the VarioCam Plus system, optimizing torque delivery and valve timing across the rev range. The chassis remains taut, utilizing its original MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry for exceptional lateral grip. Recent service includes a proactive inspection of the IMS bearing and a fresh AOS (Air Oil Separator) replacement. While showing minor patina consistent with its age, the drivetrain remains robust, delivering linear power and the signature flat-six acoustic profile. Four-piston monobloc calipers provide consistent, fade-free deceleration. A true driver-spec 911 ready for the canyons.",
